Public Sponsor: 2R02 - New York Department of Transportation - o	Adirondack Transit Lines (ATL) is a privately owned and operated bus company. In addition to operating other business lines, ATL provides dedicated commuter bus services within and between several designated Federal Transit Administration (FTA) urbanized areas. The Metropolitan Planning Organizations (MPO) within these urbanized areas have voluntarily elected to make available a portion of the amounts generated under Urbanized Area Formula Program (49 USC 5307), attributable to these commuter services, to ATL, to maintain, expand, and modernize their commuter rolling-stock and associated facilities. Pursuant to agreement, the Capital District Transportation Authority (CDTA) acts on behalf of the MPOs and serves as the administrative host for the submission of a single unified FTA grant application. CDTA annually reviews for sufficiency and verifies the eligibility of the data provided to NTD by ATL.
